================================================================================
BUNDLED THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS — mpv and FFmpeg, under the LGPL
================================================================================

This package bundles the mpv media player and FFmpeg, licensed under the GNU
Lesser General Public License (LGPL). They are NOT covered by the MIT license
above. Both platforms intentionally ship LGPL builds (never GPL builds) so a
closed-source application may link them, provided the application honors the LGPL
terms. Linkage differs by platform: Android links libmpv as a shared library
(.so); iOS links the LGPL MPVKit xcframeworks statically (see the LGPL §6 note
at the end).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
iOS / tvOS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Component:   mpv + FFmpeg, via MPVKit
Product:     "MPVKit" (LGPL v3.0) — NOT "MPVKit-GPL"
Linkage:     the LGPL MPVKit prebuilt xcframeworks (the "MPVKit" product's binary
             targets) are VENDORED by this module's pod (ios/ExpoMpvPlayer.podspec
             -> vendored_frameworks) and linked statically into the app. They are
             fetched by scripts/fetch-mpvkit-xcframeworks.sh (checksum-verified,
             LGPL-only) and are not committed to git.
FFmpeg:      built WITHOUT --enable-gpl (LGPL configuration)
Pinned:      MPVKit 0.41.0 (bundles mpv 0.41.0 + FFmpeg n8.1.1)
Source:      https://github.com/mpvkit/MPVKit  (release 0.41.0; its Package.swift
             pins the exact binary-target URLs + checksums)
License:     GNU LGPL v3.0

  mpv:    https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv      (LGPL v2.1+)
  FFmpeg: https://ffmpeg.org/                    (LGPL v2.1+, version3 enabled)

